<br>
Come on, now I don't claim to know anything about this event other than what was written here, but it sounds to me like 2 people with conflicting personalities happened to cross paths.  We can sit here and debate whether a 52 druid powerleveling her friend or a 55 ranger hunting for faction/farming/whatever has more right to be in a 20 something dungeon, but the fact of the matter is it isn't that big of a deal; hardly worth all this.  <br>
<br>
Now I haven't explicitly defended Chandalan, nor do I feel the need to try to.  I don't think he did anything wrong, but then again he is my guildmate and I have had more time to see the way he conducts himself at other times.   <br>
<br>
You sit here and condemn Vision for sticking up for it's members, while not too long ago UDL was sticking up for a UDL member that decided to ninjaloot some crappy sword from Sebilis (a far worse offense than what was commited here, IMHO).   All the while screaming things like "We support our members because they're like family, any good guild would do that" and "Anyone who would judge a whole guild based on the actions of one member is an ignorant jerk" and now Palimax is the hypocrite?    <p><CENTER>
